# Dataset Card: Validation

## Overview

The `datasets/validation/` folder contains datasets reserved for validating machine learning models, benchmark algorithms, and circuit analysis workflows within Circuit-Bench. Validation datasets are used during model development to monitor performance, tune hyperparameters, and evaluate generalization before final testing.

---

## Purpose

The validation datasets are intended to:

- Evaluate model performance during development
- Support hyperparameter optimization
- Monitor training progress
- Detect overfitting
- Assess model generalization
- Enable reproducible benchmarking

---

## Intended Applications

These datasets are suitable for:

- Machine learning validation
- Circuit classification
- Circuit regression
- Fault detection
- Benchmark evaluation
- Model selection
- Algorithm development

---

## Folder Organization

A typical directory structure may resemble:

```text
validation/
├── analog/
├── digital/
├── passive/
├── active/
├── rf/
├── power_electronics/
├── mixed_signal/
├── metadata/
└── README.md
```

The organization may expand as new benchmark tasks are introduced.

---

## Dataset Contents

Validation datasets may include:

- Circuit netlists
- Schematics
- Simulation results
- Feature matrices
- Labels
- Metadata
- Reference outputs
- Annotation files

---

## Data Quality

Validation datasets should undergo rigorous quality assurance, including:

- Manual verification
- Duplicate detection
- Metadata validation
- Schema validation
- Label consistency checks
- File integrity verification

---

## Recommended Usage

Researchers are encouraged to:

- Use validation data only during model development.
- Keep validation datasets separate from testing datasets.
- Avoid modifying validation labels.
- Record validation dataset versions in publications.
- Report evaluation metrics consistently.

---

## Reproducibility

To facilitate reproducible research, users should document:

- Dataset version
- Validation protocol
- Software version
- Model configuration
- Random seed (if applicable)

---

## Example Workflow

```text
Training Dataset
        │
        ▼
Model Training
        │
        ▼
Validation Dataset
        │
        ▼
Hyperparameter Tuning
        │
        ▼
Final Model
        │
        ▼
Testing Dataset
```

---

## Limitations

Validation datasets may not:

- Represent all real-world circuit designs
- Cover every circuit topology
- Include every component technology
- Capture all manufacturing variations

Performance on validation datasets may not directly translate to unseen real-world data.

---

## Best Practices

Users should:

- Never train directly on validation data.
- Avoid repeated tuning on the same validation split.
- Maintain clear separation between training, validation, and testing datasets.
- Report validation methodology transparently.

